The Media Division consists of two free-to-air (FTA) television channels. SCTV is one of Indonesia’s leading nationwide free-to-air channels with audiences in excess of 160 million viewers in more than 240 cities across the country. The Jakarta-based O Channel provides free-to-air lifestyle and entertainment programming for the capital. The Solutions Division provides a range of infrastructure and information, communication and technology solutions for the telecommunication, banking and retail payment industries, including service solutions for integrated VSAT, smart card infrastructure and the retail distribution of telecommunications services.

Description: MedcoEnergi is an oil and gas company.
Full Description: MedcoEnergi  as a Private National Oil & Gas Company and its partners has succeeded in monetizing the Senoro gas field which was previously considered as stranded gas, by supplying gas to the Donggi Senoro LNG plant among others. The inauguration of both projects was in conjunction with the release of first cargo of LNG shipment by the President of the Republic of Indonesia, Mr. Joko Widodo. Senoro Gas Development, one of MedcoEnergi's major developments, was once considered stranded gas due to its remote location and unavailability of infrastructure for the gas captives. We successfully develop and monetize the abundant gas resources into high quality markets that will take gas up to 310 mmscf per day. In January 2015, MedcoEnergi inked a Gas Sales Agreement of over US$ 2 billion in value, monetizing 200 BCF reserves from the Block A Production Sharing Contract in Aceh Province, Indonesia. The customer is the state owned company Pertamina, with an agreed gas price of US$ 9.45 per MMBTU. This contract demonstrates the Company’s support to the development of the Indonesian domestic gas market, at the same time creating value for the company and establishing a vital economic presence in the province of Aceh.

Description: MNC Corporation began in the financial service industry as a brokerage house and has evolved to become Indonesia's leading investment group.

It went public on the Indonesian Stock Exchange in 1997. Under the leadership of its founder and Group CEO, Hary Tanoesoedibjo, MNC Corporation focuses on 3 strategic investments: Media, Financial Services, Property and Portfolio Investments. In the media sector, operated under its subsidiary Global Mediacom or known as MNC Media, MNC Group own the largest and the most integrated media in South East Asia, with a portfolio of free to air TV stations, Pay TV platforms and online business. In advertising related business, MNC owns four national free to air stations. Being the largest TV station in Indonesia, RCTI specializes in family drama series and major entertainment programs. Some major programs produced by RCTI include Indonesian Idol, Master Chef, X Factor and Rising Star. MNCTV focuses on variety shows, traditional type of drama and live sports. And Global TV entertains kids and young adults with hollywood movies and cartoons. MNC also owns iNews TV, the largest national TV network, comprising 51 local TV stations across Indonesia with focus on news programs operates 22 Pay TV channels under the MNC family brand and has the largest content library of more than 270,000 hours. iNews TV network and Pay TV channels will become an important source of future growth for MNC Media.

Description: Bisnis is a daily newspaper, covering Indonesian financial and business news and issues.
Full Description: Bisnis is a daily newspaper, covering Indonesian financial and business news and issues. The newspaper gained its momentum from the rise of stock market in 1987 and new policy in banking known as Paket Oktober 1998. Then it shifted its coverage to focus on micro-economics and business news, in the time when most competitors still reporting heavily on macro-economic issue. Bisnis also supplies news content for international news agencies, including Japan-based NewsNet Asia, [Factiva](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/factiva) and joint venture Dow Jones, [Reuters](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/reuters), and [ISI Emerging Markets](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/isi-emerging-markets) owned by Euromoney Institutional Investor Group, Chinese news agency Xinhua, and [Bloomberg](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/bloomberg). Bisnis is published in Jakarta, Indonesia by PT Jurnalindo Aksara Grafika, a company founded by three conglomerate businessmen in Indonesia that include Sukamdani Sahid Gitosardjono, Ciputra, Anthony Salim, and media veteran Eric FH Samola. It was first published in 1985.

Nihiwatu, Sumba - East Indonesia. Unregulated freedom, understated luxury and unforgettable memories.
Full Description: The story of NIHIWATU® is a rare and fascinating tale that began when Sumba’s ancestors, the ‘Marapu,’ landed on its secluded beach centuries ago. Beliefs about their powers vary, but the Marapu spirit has remained a benevolent force on the island, protecting the way of life and attracting custodians whom honor and carry forth the heritage and stories of the Sumbanese people, past and present. The same beach attracted Claude and Petra Graves in 1988, in search of the perfect wave. From this adventure emerged a vision to create a resort that would preserve and share the breathtaking beauty of Sumba with those who would truly appreciate it. NIHIWATU® beach, meaning “mortar stone,” was named by early settlers for its isolated rock formation along the tide. The Graves aptly called the resort Nihiwatu for its surrounding legacy.

Spirit Studios was always at the heart of the Manchester music scene and producers such as Trevor Horn (Frankie Goes To Hollywood/Seal etc); Martin Hannet (Stone Roses, Joy Division etc); Arthur Baker (Bruce Springsteen; Bob Dylan; Kraftwerk; Al Green); all visited Spirit to record and produce their work. Wika Water Heater is ultimate renewable energy products: solar water heater, ac water heater and photovoltaic made in Indonesia
Full Description: Wika Water Heater has been named as the first domestic brands in Indonesia as water heaters that use solar power and air conditioning. The Wika brand under the auspices of PT Wijaya Karya Industri Energi has long been known to be a company that continues to develop innovations in the world of technology to meet the needs of the community. Some of the innovations are water heating technology from sunlight, using technology from AC, there is also a heat pump water heater and an electric water heater. One of Wika Water Heater advantage is domestic products and there is a guaranteed after-sales service. Because Wika's products are available everywhere and always ready to help. Since 1988, Wika has been developing water heaters with solar energy. In its development, Wika Industri Energi complements its water heating products other than SWH, namely by making a Water Heater HeatPump, Aircon Water Heater (AWH) and a photo voltaic system (PV) that converts solar energy into electrical energy using mono/poly chrystalin technology. This photo voltaic system produces electricity from solar cell technology. There is a Ministerial Regulation on Roof Top in 2018. There is a meter that measures the energy produced by this photo voltaic. Since 1987, technical experts who are members of WIKA in the Industrial Equipment Division in collaboration with several technical experts from ITB and BPPT have succeeded in designing the concept and design of the first Solar Water Heater product in Indonesia, which is oriented towards meeting the hot water needs of the household segment. Furthermore, this product was introduced and marketed to the public in 1988 under the WIKA SWH brand. The WIKA SWH application for the industrial segment with large capacity has also been started since 1992. Wika Water Heater was awarded as the TOP BRAND 2011 and 2012 for the category of water heater products. It's a trust from Indonesian consumers on quality, marketing performance and after-sales service that must be maintained and developed. Wijaya Karya Energi Industries has also been certified ISO 9001:2015 quality management. Wika believe and believe that we can continue to serve consumers with the best products and services. As instilled in the Company's Values, namely ACE: Agility, Caring, Excellent. A Corporate Value that underlies us to work optimally to achieve the dream of becoming a leading national company. WIKA also implement various other quality management systems to measure the progress and sustainable development of the company such as the Malcolm Baldridge Criteria for Performance Excellence, WIN Scorecard, 5S and OHSAS.
